# mq configuration file
#
# Config files are loaded in order (later overrides earlier):
#   1. ~/.mqrc                    Global defaults (copy this file there)
#   2. ./.mqrc                    Project-local overrides
#      ./.mqrc.dist               (fallback if .mqrc missing)
#
# Typical workflow: commit .mqrc.dist to version control with shared
# defaults, add .mqrc to .gitignore for local customization.
#
# This file is sourced as bash, so you can use any valid bash syntax:
# conditionals, environment variables, command substitution, etc.

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MYSQL_OPTIONS - MySQL client options
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# An array of options passed directly to the mysql client.
# Use += to append to the defaults (recommended) or = to replace entirely.
#
# Common options:
#   --database=NAME, -D NAME    Database to use
#   --host=HOST, -h HOST        Server hostname (default: localhost)
#   --port=PORT, -P PORT        Server port (default: 3306)
#   --socket=PATH, -S PATH      Unix socket path
#   --user=USER, -u USER        Username for authentication
#   --password=PASS, -p[PASS]   Password (omit value to prompt)
#   --protocol=PROTO            Connection protocol (tcp, socket, pipe, memory)
#   --ssl-mode=MODE             SSL mode (DISABLED, PREFERRED, REQUIRED, etc.)
#   --connect-timeout=SEC       Connection timeout in seconds
#   --compress, -C              Use compression in client/server protocol
#   --default-character-set=CS  Character set (e.g., utf8mb4)
#
# For the full list, see: mysql --help
#
# Examples:
#   MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--database=myapp)
#   MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--host=db.example.com --port=3306)
#   MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--user=readonly --password=secret)
#   MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--ssl-mode=REQUIRED)
#
# Using environment variables:
#   MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--database="${MYSQL_DATABASE:-myapp}")
#   MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--host="${MYSQL_HOST:-localhost}")
#
# Conditional configuration:
#   if [[ "$HOSTNAME" == *prod* ]]; then
#       MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--host=prod-db.internal)
#   else
#       MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--host=localhost)
#   fi

# MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--database=mydb)
# MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--host=localhost)
# MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--user=myuser)

# Using a MySQL defaults file:
#   Instead of specifying credentials in .mqrc, you can point to an
#   existing MySQL option file (e.g., ~/.my.cnf or a project-specific one).
#   --defaults-file replaces all default option files:
#     MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--defaults-file="$HOME/.my.cnf")
#   --defaults-extra-file loads additional options after the defaults:
#     MYSQL_OPTIONS+=(--defaults-extra-file=".my.cnf")

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FORMAT - Default output format
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Controls how query results are displayed.
#
# Acceptable values:
#   tsv       Tab-separated values, no headers (default)
#             Best for: piping to awk, cut, or other CLI tools
#
#   table     ASCII table with borders and column headers
#             Best for: human-readable output in the terminal
#
#   vertical  One column per line (\G style)
#             Best for: wide rows that don't fit on screen
#
#   html      HTML table format
#             Best for: generating reports or web content
#
#   xml       XML format with row/field elements
#             Best for: machine processing or data interchange
#
#   csv       Comma-separated values with headers (RFC 4180)
#             Best for: data interchange, spreadsheet import, exports
#
# Can be overridden per-query with: -f, --format
# Can also use trailing + on query for vertical format.

# FORMAT=tsv

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# QUIET - Suppress query echo
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When set to 1, suppresses printing the query to stderr before execution.
# By default (0), the query is displayed dimmed above the results.
#
# Acceptable values:
#   0    Show query before results (default)
#   1    Hide query, show only results
#
# Can be overridden per-query with: -q, --quiet

# QUIET=0
